We recommended that Management:

Reconcile the discrepancies noted in the LDRRMF balances in CY 2016 and 2017;

Determine the amount of unutilized Mitigation Fund – Maintenance and Operating Expenses (MOOE) and Mitigation Fund – Capital Outlay (CO) for CYs 2013-2018 by classifying projects with unutilized balances as of December 31, 2018 into MOOE and CO;

Effect the correcting entry to adjust the balance of the Trust Liability-DRRM account by the amount of unutilized LDRRMF for CYs 2013 to 2017 for capital outlay using the proposed pro-forma entry;

Transfer the unutilized Quick Response Fund (QRF) and LDRRMF- MOOE balance in CY 2018; and

Ensure accurate and timely recording of the transactions related to the transfer and utilization of the current LDRRMF and the unspent prior year balance of the subject fund and its proper presentation in the Financial Statements.

